# CropAbility documentation rules

## Location

All **project documentation** belongs under **`doc/`** or root **`README.md`**:

| Doc | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `doc/TODO.md` | Master M1 checklist (`M1-*` IDs); checkbox truth source |
| `doc/TODO_PROGRESS_LOG.md` | Dated completion log (required for each closed item) |
| `doc/TODO_PROGRESS_SYNC.md` | Vault / GitHub sync mapping (Obsidian `3.CropAbility/`) |
| `doc/TESTING.md` | Pytest layout, markers, publish vs dev assets |
| `doc/RUST_DEVELOPMENT.md` | PyO3, Cargo features, maturin |
| `doc/PYTHON_DEVELOPMENT.md` | Python API; legacy PGL blocks are archive reference only |
| `README.md` | User-facing install and usage |

Do **not** create `README.md` or architecture notes under `src/test/` or `src/main/python/`.

## Language

Follow `english-only.mdc` for all doc text.

## Content alignment

When updating docs, reflect current architecture:

- Python host → Rust extension; no Java, no TorchScript, no `scripts/`.
- Single root `Cargo.toml`; tests in `src/test/python/`.
- Resources in `src/main/resources/`; models not vendored in repo.

Keep `doc/PYTHON_DEVELOPMENT.md` legacy PGL sections clearly labeled as historical, not the supported API.
